title: Introduction
---

<Header />

<Frame id="hero" intent="hero-section">
  <div className="tk-hero">
    <h1>Your product films its own demo.</h1>
    <p>
      Wrap a region in <code>&lt;TelekineticFrame&gt;</code>, mount{" "}
      <code>&lt;TelekinesisStage&gt;</code>, and Telekinesis choreographs the zooms,
      spotlights, ghost-cursor moves and typing — captured to <strong>video or GIF</strong>{" "}
      by Playwright, narrated by a declarative <em>timesheet</em>.
    </p>
    <Frame id="hero-cta" intent="primary-action">
      <a className="tk-cta" href="/getting-started">Start recording →</a>
    </Frame>
  </div>
</Frame>

<DemoGif section="hero" caption="This page is a Telekinetic app. Press ▶ Play live to watch it perform its own tour." />

This very site is the demo target: the docs are marked up with frames, and every
motion example below was recorded by Telekinesis recording **itself**.

<Frame id="pillars" intent="feature-grid">
  <div className="tk-pillars">
    <Frame id="pillar-motion" intent="feature-card">
      <div className="tk-pillar">
        <h3>🎞️ Motion-first</h3>
        <p>Eased zooms, spotlights and a ghost cursor — the camera language editors reach for, driven entirely by data.</p>
      </div>
    </Frame>
    <Frame id="pillar-ai" intent="feature-card">
      <div className="tk-pillar">
        <h3>🤖 AI-authored</h3>
        <p>An MCP agent drafts a schema-valid timesheet from your live frames; you refine the pacing.</p>
      </div>
    </Frame>
    <Frame id="pillar-ci" intent="feature-card">
      <div className="tk-pillar">
        <h3>⚙️ CI-friendly</h3>
        <p>Headless Playwright + ffmpeg produce a fresh MP4 or GIF on every merge — no manual capture.</p>
      </div>
    </Frame>
  </div>
</Frame>

<Divider />

## Where to next

- **[Getting started](/getting-started)** — mark up your UI and record in five minutes.
- **[Concepts](/concepts)** — one component, two lives; the registry; the overlay.
- **[Effects](/effects)** — the full cinematic vocabulary, each shown in motion.
